Title : Debout Les Belges!
Text : '''Debout Les Belges!''' (Belgians, Rise up!) is a political group in [[Belgium]], founded and led by avowedly [[anti-Zionist]] [[Chamber of Representatives (Belgium)|Belgian MP]] [[Laurent Louis]], who was previously associated with the [[Islamist]] party {{ill|ISLAM (Belgian political party)|lt=ISLAM|fr|ISLAM (parti politique belge)|nl|Islam (politieke partij)|es|Islam (partido político)}}.{{citation needed|date=May 2014}}

The group is associated with [[France|French]] comedian [[Dieudonné M'bala M'bala]] and the [[quenelle (gesture)|quenelle gesture]] which he has popularized, often considered a subversive allusion to the [[Nazi salute]].<ref name=one>{{cite web | url=https://www.asiaone.com/world/belgium-bans-anti-semitic-hatefest | title=Belgium bans 'anti-Semitic hatefest'}}</ref> Although its leader has recently criticized [[Alain Soral]], another important leader of [[Reconciliation Nationale]].<ref name="four">{{cite web | url=https://www.facebook.com/laurentlouisdlb/posts/1826597107622288 | title=Laurent LOUIS - Debout Les Belges officiel}}</ref> The group has been accused of [[antisemitism]] and a planned gathering of notable anti-Zionists organized by Louis was banned in 2014.<ref name="one"/><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.albawaba.com/photo-week/leader-debout-les-belges-far-right-lawmaker-laurent-louis-c-perform-quenelle-gesture-ahea | title=The leader of "Debout Les Belges!," far-right lawmaker Laurent Louis (C) perform the 'quenelle' gesture ahead of the anti-Semitic congress, "First European Conference of Dissidence", organised by Chamber member Laurent Louis in Anderlecht, outside Brussel | dead-url=yes | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140508133942/https://www.albawaba.com/photo-week/leader-debout-les-belges-far-right-lawmaker-laurent-louis-c-perform-quenelle-gesture-ahea | archive-date=May 8, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.israelnationalnews.com/News/News.aspx/180243 | title=Belgium: Riot Police Disperse Anti-Semitic Rally}}</ref>

